","Of Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Alstone, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1590–7 Mar 1633":"1590–7. marts 1633","1586–1665":"1586–1665","1615–1642":"1615–1642","1616–Male":"1616–Afdød","1620–1690":"1620–1690","1625–Male":"1625–Afdød","1590–1633":"1590–1633","ABT 1620":"omkring 1620","1690":"1690","1590":"1590","1633":"1633","1665":"1665","1620":"1620","1642":"1642","1586":"1586","10 July 1614":"10. juli 1614","29 January 1616":"29. januar 1616","26 August 1615":"26. august 1615","1616":"1616","7 Mar 1633":"7. marts 1633","1615":"1615","15 April 1625":"15. april 1625","1625":"1625","Alstone, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, England","Of Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Alstone, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1590–7 Mar 1633":"1590–7 maart 1633","1586–1665":"1586–1665","1615–1642":"1615–1642","1616–Male":"1616–Overleden","1620–1690":"1620–1690","1625–Male":"1625–Overleden","1590–1633":"1590–1633","ABT 1620":"circa 1620","1690":"1690","1590":"1590","1633":"1633","1665":"1665","1620":"1620","1642":"1642","1586":"1586","10 July 1614":"10 juli 1614","29 January 1616":"29 januari 1616","26 August 1615":"26 augustus 1615","1616":"1616","7 Mar 1633":"7 maart 1633","1615":"1615","15 April 1625":"15 april 1625","1625":"1625","Alstone, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, England","Of Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Alstone, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1590–7 Mar 1633":"1590–7 March 1633","1586–1665":"1586–1665","1615–1642":"1615–1642","1616–Male":"1616–Deceased","1620–1690":"1620–1690","1625–Male":"1625–Deceased","1590–1633":"1590–1633","ABT 1620":"about 1620","1690":"1690","1590":"1590","1633":"1633","1665":"1665","1620":"1620","1642":"1642","1586":"1586","10 July 1614":"10 July 1614","29 January 1616":"29 January 1616","26 August 1615":"26 August 1615","1616":"1616","7 Mar 1633":"7 March 1633","1615":"1615","15 April 1625":"15 April 1625","1625":"1625","Alstone, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, England","Of Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Alstone, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"George","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Welsh, French, and Romanian: from the personal name <i>George</i>, Latin <i>Georgius</i>, Greek <i>Geōrgios</i>, from an adjectival form, <i>geōrgios</i> ‘rustic’, of Greek <i>geōrgos</i> ‘farmer’. This became established as a personal name in classical times through its association with the fashion for pastoral poetry. Its popularity in western Europe increased at the time of the Crusades, which brought greater contact with the Orthodox Church, in which several Christian martyrs and saints of this name are venerated, in particular a saint believed to have been martyred at Nicomedia in  AD  303, who, however, is at best a shadowy figure historically. Nevertheless, by the end of the Middle Ages Saint George had become associated with an unhistorical legend of dragon-slaying exploits, which caught the popular imagination throughout Europe, and he came to be considered the patron saint of England among other places. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed many cognates from other languages, e.g. German   Georg  , Assyrian/Chaldean <b>Giwargis</b>,   Gewargis  , or   Georgis  , and Albanian   Gjergji  , and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Greek   Georgiadis  ,   Georgopoulos  , <b>Hatzigeorgiou</b> ‘George the Pilgrim’, and   Papageorgiou  , Romanian   Georgescu   or <b>Gheorghescu</b>, Serbian   Djordjevic  . The name <i>George</i> is also found among Christians in southern India (compare   Geevarghese   and   Varghese  ), but since South Indians traditionally do not have hereditary surnames, the southern Indian name was in most cases registered as such only after immigration of its bearers to the US.","German: variant of   Georg  .","Native American (e.g. Navajo): adoption of the English personal name <i>George</i> (see 1 above) as a surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Djordjevic","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Serbian or Croatian Dragan, Bozidar, Branko, Milan, Miodrag, Momcilo, Predrag, Sinisa, Sotir, Borka, Djordje, Dragana, Dunja, Dusan, Mirko, Miroslav, Milutin, Misha, Vladimir.","Serbian and Croatian (<b>Djordjević</b>, standard spelling <b>Đorđević</b>): patronymic from the especially Serbian personal name <i>Đorđe</i>, from Greek <i>Geōrgios</i> (see   George  ). <i>Đorđević</i> is the fifth most frequent surname in Serbia. Compare   Georgevich  ."]},{"name":"Djukic","meanings":["Serbian and Croatian (<b>Djukić</b>, standard spelling <b>Đukić</b>): patronymic from a pet form of the personal name <i>Đurađ</i>, from Greek <i>Geōrgios</i> (see   George  )."]},{"name":"Durko","meanings":["Slovak (<b>Ďurko</b>): from the personal name <i>Ďurko</i>, a pet form of <i>Juraj</i>, an equivalent of   George  . Compare   Darko  ."]},{"name":"Gazzo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Almando, Attilio, Julio, Salvatore.","Italian: probably from the medieval Greek personal name <i>Gatsos</i>, a pet form of <i>Georgatsos</i>, a derivative of <i>Geōrgios</i> (see   George  ). Alternatively, a nickname from Sicilian <i>gazzu</i> ‘blue-eyed’ (also ‘short-sighted’), or from Old Italian <i>gazzo</i> ‘deep blue’ (like the feathers of a magpie, Italian <i>gazza</i>). It could also be a habitational name from Gazzo in Padova province, Gazzo Veronese in Verona province, or from a shortened form of <i>Agazzo</i>, from Late Latin <i>Agathius</i>, either a masculine form of <i>Agata</i> or from the analogous ancient Germanic personal name <i>Agathio</i>."]},{"name":"Geevarghese","meanings":["Indian (Kerala): from the personal name <i>Geevarghese</i>, a derivative of Greek <i>Geōrgios</i> (see   George  ), found among Christians in southern India. — Note: Since South Indians traditionally do not have hereditary surnames, this name was in most cases registered as such only after immigration of its bearers to the US."]},{"name":"Ganta","meanings":["Indian (Andhra Pradesh): name borne by a sept of Kamma (agrarian) and Balija (trader) people, from Telugu <i>ganta</i> ‘bell’.","Romanian (<b>Ganţă</b>): from a derivative of the personal name <i>Gană</i>, <i>Gane</i>, <i>Ganu</i>, of Bulgarian origin (a pet form of local names corresponding to   George  )."]},{"name":"Durica","meanings":["Slovak and Czech (Moravian) (<b>Ďurica</b>): patronymic from the personal name <i>Ďuro</i>, a vernacular form of local equivalents (<i>Juraj</i>, <i>Jura</i>) of Latin <i>Georgius</i> (see   George  )."]},{"name":"Djuric","meanings":["Serbian and Croatian (<b>Djurić</b>, standard spelling <b>Đurić</b>): patronymic from the personal names <i>Đura</i> and <i>Đuro</i>, short forms of <i>Đurađ</i>, from Greek <i>Geōrgios</i> (see   George  ). See also   Juric  , compare   Duric  ."]},{"name":"Georg","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erwin, Gerd, Kurt, Manfred.","German: from the personal name <i>Georg</i>, an equivalent of Latin <i>Georgius</i> (see   George  )."]},{"name":"Djokic","meanings":["Serbian (<b>Djokić</b>, standard spelling <b>Đokić</b>): patronymic from a pet form of the personal name <i>Đorđe</i>, from Greek <i>Geōrgios</i> (see   George  )."]}]},{"name":"Susanna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Suzannah","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."]},{"name":"Suzanna","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."]},{"name":"Susana","meanings":["From Hebrew.  See  <b>Susanna</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Susanna George was born in 1590, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. She married Richard Peart on 10 July 1614, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died on 7 March 1633, in her hometown, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1590–7 Mar 1633":"1590–7. märts 1633","1586–1665":"1586–1665","1615–1642":"1615–1642","1616–Male":"1616–Surnud","1620–1690":"1620–1690","1625–Male":"1625–Surnud","1590–1633":"1590–1633","ABT 1620":"umbes 1620","1690":"1690","1590":"1590","1633":"1633","1665":"1665","1620":"1620","1642":"1642","1586":"1586","10 July 1614":"10. juuli 1614","29 January 1616":"29. jaanuar 1616","26 August 1615":"26. august 1615","1616":"1616","7 Mar 1633":"7. märts 1633","1615":"1615","15 April 1625":"15. aprill 1625","1625":"1625","Alstone, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, England","Of Alstone, Gloucestershire, England":"Alstone, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alstone, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1590–7 Mar 1633":"1590–7. maaliskuuta 1633","1586–1665":"1586–1665","1615–1642":"1615–1642","1616–Male":"1616–Kuollut","